        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My 800 Series with CrystalDry isn't drying properly",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "CrystalDry uses a zeolite mineral canister that absorbs humidity and releases heat during the drying cycle — unique to 800 Series and Benchmark. When drying performance drops, three possibilities: (1) zeolite canister saturated and not regenerating properly — happens on 4-6 year old units where the zeolite has absorbed enough scale and detergent residue that its heat-release capacity is reduced; canister replacement $285-$385; (2) heating element failed (E09 code usually accompanies) — $185-$265; (3) rinse aid dispenser empty or clogged — water doesn't sheet off properly, stays on dishes; dispenser refill is free maintenance. We check zeolite regeneration cycle performance via Home Connect data (if enabled) before ordering parts."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does Bosch dishwasher repair cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Diagnostic is $89, waived with repair. Typical Bosch dishwasher repairs: circulation pump assembly (00654575 on 300/500/800) $285-$385, drain pump $185-$265, heating element $185-$265, water inlet valve $165-$245, Aquastop hose assembly $145-$215, float switch (00611316 or 12019637) $185-$265, door latch $145-$215, door gasket $195-$285, spray arm (upper or lower) $85-$165, detergent dispenser $125-$195, control board (main PCB) $385-$580, user interface touchpad $285-$425, CrystalDry zeolite canister (800/Benchmark) $285-$385, diverter motor (E26) $145-$215, aqua sensor (E06/E28) $125-$185, turbidity sensor $95-$155, filter cleaning (no parts, preventive) $95 flat, Home Connect firmware update (no parts) $85 flat. Labor and parts quoted before work starts."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can firmware update fix my Bosch dishwasher issue?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Sometimes. 2020+ 500, 800, and Benchmark Series dishwashers with Home Connect can receive firmware updates that resolve specific intermittent errors — particularly on 2021-2022 units where early firmware had known issues. About 15% of 'intermittent error' complaints on these units resolve via firmware update without any parts replacement. We check firmware version during diagnostic: look for update available in the Home Connect app, run update via WiFi, test cycle. $85 flat for firmware service when that's all that's needed. If your dishwasher isn't connected to Home Connect but the model supports it, we can walk you through setup as part of the service call — some persistent errors won't be resolvable without the update path."
        }
