      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why does my Bosch dishwasher have no display but flash error lights?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Lower-tier Bosch models (100 Series and some 300 Series) don't have a digital display — errors show as blinking-light patterns on the control panel. Count the blinks: specific patterns map to E-codes documented in the service manual. Common patterns: water-inlet light flashing continuously = E16/E17/E18 (water fill issue), drain light flashing = E22/E24/E25 (drainage), door light + start light = E15 (anti-flood). We bring the code reference chart on every call; owner doesn't need to decode it. If the blinks don't match any known pattern, we use diagnostic mode access (different sequence per model family) to retrieve the actual stored code."
