        <div class="hero-img-placeholder">
          <p>Bosch Dishwasher Repair</p>
          <p>Los Angeles</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="trust-bar">
    <div class="trust-bar-inner">
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🏅</span> CSLB Licensed #1138898</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🛡</span> Fully Insured</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">⚡</span> Same Day Available</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🔩</span> OEM Parts on Truck</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">💬</span> $89 Diagnostic — Waived With Repair</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">About this service</p>
      <h2>The Bosch dishwasher is arguably the best residential dishwasher in North America.</h2>
      <p>If Bosch was known for just one appliance category, it would be dishwashers. Consistently top-rated by Consumer Reports and Reviewed. Uniformly quieter than competitors at every price tier — 44 dB on 800 Series versus 50+ dB for most competitors in the same range. CrystalDry zeolite drying (800 Series and Benchmark) actually dries plastic containers properly, unlike almost every other dishwasher on the market. And the 485-point quality check process Bosch runs on every unit means the failure rate is genuinely lower than GE, Whirlpool, or KitchenAid at equivalent price points.</p>
      <p>When Bosch dishwashers do need service, the engineering helps us work quickly. Error codes (E01 through E30) map to specific components with documented diagnostic paths. OEM part numbers are consistent across the 300/500/800 platforms — float switch 00611316 covers the vast majority of post-2005 Bosch dishwashers, circulation pump 00654575 covers most SHE/SHP/SHX models. <strong>Thermador dishwashers share the Bosch platform exactly</strong> — same parts, same diagnostic procedures, same service approach. We carry common Bosch/Thermador parts on every truck.</p>
      <p>Most of our Bosch dishwasher calls are 3-to-8-year-old 300, 500, or 800 Series units past the 1-year base warranty — Brentwood, Santa Monica, Mid-Wilshire, West Hollywood, and Culver City new construction from 2018-2022 that's seeing first post-warranty service needs now. Factory-trained service at a lower labor rate than Bosch authorized dispatch.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── MODELS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Platforms and models</p>
      <h2>Bosch dishwasher models we service</h2>

      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>100 Series (Entry)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">SHE3AR7 · SHEM3AY · SHEM63W · SHX3AR7</p>
          <p>Basic Bosch dishwasher with stainless tub (on most 100 Series models), 50 dB noise level, 4 cycles. No digital display — errors show as blinking-light patterns on the control panel. Common in rental properties and builder-spec kitchens. Parts availability excellent; repair costs are the lowest across Bosch tiers because the platform is simpler.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>300 Series (Mid-Entry)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">SHE3AR7 · SHX3AR7 · SHS863WD5N · SHXM63WS5N · SHE53B77</p>
          <p>Stainless tub standard, improved drying with dedicated heating element (not zeolite-based), 46 dB, 5 cycles. Digital display on most units. Most common Bosch in mid-market new construction across LA 2018-2024. Workhorse tier — strong parts availability, excellent repair economics.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>500 Series (Mid)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">SHP65CC5UC · SHPM65Z55N · SHP865ZD5N · SHPM65W55N · SHP878ZD5N</p>
          <p>PureDry drying technology, 44 dB (noticeably quieter than 300), 6 cycles including Speed60 for fast washing. Third rack for silverware. Home Connect WiFi on 2020+ units. Common in mid-luxury builds across Brentwood, Santa Monica, and Westwood where 800 Series was not specified but owner wanted above-mid-market performance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>800 Series (Premium Flagship)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">SHP78CM5N · SHP878ZD5N · SHPM78Z55N · SHXM78Z55N · SHEM78Z55N · SHX878ZD5N</p>
          <p>CrystalDry zeolite drying (Bosch's best, dries plastics properly), 42-44 dB, 8 cycles including Extra Shine and PowerControl, PrecisionWash sensor technology, Home Connect WiFi standard. Most common Bosch dishwasher in LA luxury kitchens. Zeolite canister is a service item around year 4-6.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Benchmark (Flagship)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">SHV878ZD3N · SHE878ZD5N · SHX878ZD5N · SHP878ZD5N (Benchmark variants)</p>
          <p>38 dB operation (quietest Bosch makes), ball-bearing rack systems with smoother glide, interior lighting, full-color LCD displays. Same CrystalDry zeolite and PrecisionWash as 800 Series. Fundamental engineering is shared with 800 Series — service parts largely the same with some Benchmark-specific trim items.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Thermador (Same Platform)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">DWHD650 · DWHD660 · DWHD770 · DWHD870 · Star Sapphire</p>
          <p>Thermador dishwashers are built on the Bosch platform with Thermador trim and branding. Float switch 00611316 and circulation pump 00654575 are identical to Bosch 300/500/800. Service procedures identical. If you have a Thermador dishwasher, we service it the same way as a Bosch equivalent — see our <a href="/brands/thermador-dishwasher-repair/" style="color: var(--red);">Thermador dishwasher page</a> for Thermador-specific positioning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="footnote">Model number prefix key: SHE = front control, full console. SHX = fully integrated (controls on top edge, invisible from front). SHP = front control with pocket handle. SHV = fully integrated panel-ready (custom cabinet panel). SHS = front control with towel-bar handle. SHPM/SHXM/SHEM = M-variant with specific feature combinations.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── ERROR CODES ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Bosch E-code decoder</p>
      <h2>Complete Bosch dishwasher error code reference</h2>
      <p>Bosch dishwashers display error codes as E01 through E30 on models with digital displays, or as blinking-light patterns on 100 Series and some older units. Here's the decoder for all codes we see in the field, organized by system.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning &amp; diagnostic</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>E01 – E05</strong></td><td>Control board / power module fault. Technician required. $385-$580 board replacement. Most common on 8+ year units.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E06</strong></td><td>Aqua sensor fault. Turbidity/water-clarity sensor drifted. $95-$155 replacement.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E09</strong></td><td>Heating element burnout OR solder joint on heater relay (control board). Element $185-$265, board $385-$580 if relay side.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E12</strong></td><td>Limescale buildup warning. LA hard water accelerates this. Descale the machine; error clears. Cycle still completes but performance drops. Free DIY fix.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E15</strong></td><td>Anti-flood float switch triggered — water in base pan. Shut water off. Find and repair leak source (inlet valve, gasket, pump seal, Aquastop hose). Float switch part 00611316 (300/500/800) or 12019637 (Benchmark). $185-$265 float + leak repair.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E16 / E17 / E18</strong></td><td>Water fill / flow problem — level too low, supply valve closed, inlet hose kinked, or filling system fault. Check supply first (free), then inlet valve $165-$245.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E19</strong></td><td>Detergent dispenser solenoid fault. Dispenser $125-$195.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E20 / E21</strong></td><td>Heating / heat-pump internal faults (model-dependent). Component specific — we diagnose on site.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E22</strong></td><td>Fine filter blocked — residual water in sump. Clean filter (bottom of cavity under spray arm). 80% resolve free. Recurring E22 = filter damaged ($45-$85).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E23 / E24</strong></td><td>Drainage at intermediate stage — drain hose kinked, drain pump cover loose, garbage disposal plug not removed. Free fixes or $245-$385 pump.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E25</strong></td><td>Drain pump blockage at nozzle/impeller. Debris (glass shards, plastic) jammed pump. Remove and clean impeller — or pump replacement $245-$385.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E26</strong></td><td>Diverter motor fault. Motor controls water distribution between upper and lower spray arms. Replacement $145-$215.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E27</strong></td><td>Low voltage — dishwasher won't run (safety cutoff). Check circuit breaker, voltage at outlet (should be 120V ±5%). Not typically a dishwasher part issue.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E28</strong></td><td>Aqua sensor malfunction (same family as E06). $95-$155 replacement.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E29</strong></td><td>Low mains voltage — typically electrical-supply issue, not dishwasher internal.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>E30</strong></td><td>Voltage too high (>240V). Electrical diagnosis needed; not typically a Bosch part issue.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p><strong>For 100 Series and older units without digital display:</strong> errors show as blinking-light patterns. Water-inlet light flashing = E16/E17/E18 family. Drain-related light = E22/E24/E25. Door light + start light = E15. We carry the code reference chart on every call, so you don't need to decode the patterns yourself.</p>
      <p><strong>Reset procedure:</strong> hold Start button for 3-5 seconds (model-dependent). If code doesn't clear, turn off at breaker for 30 seconds, turn back on. Persistent codes after reset indicate a real hardware issue requiring service.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── COMMON PROBLEMS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Common failures</p>
      <h2>The ten things that break on a Bosch dishwasher</h2>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>1. E15 — water in base pan, anti-flood triggered</h3>
        <p>Most serious Bosch dishwasher call. Safety system shut the machine down to prevent water damage. Shut off water supply at the valve first. Six possible leak sources in diagnostic order: (1) inlet valve slow drip (sealer worn, allows seep when idle — $165-$245); (2) Aquastop supply hose internal leak (dual-line hose with integrated flood sensor — looks fine externally, leaks inside jacket — $145-$215); (3) door gasket worn or misaligned ($195-$285); (4) circulation pump seal failing ($285-$385 pump); (5) spray arm connection loose (free fix); (6) sump cracked (rare — $385+ replacement). After leak repair: drain the base pan, reset float switch. Without fixing the leak, E15 returns within days.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>2. E22 / E24 / E25 — drainage problems</h3>
        <p>Start with free fixes: clean the fine filter at the bottom of the tub (remove spray arm, lift filter combination, rinse under warm water, reinstall). Fixes 80% of E22 and 50% of E24 codes. Then check drain hose behind the dishwasher for kinks. Verify garbage disposal plug was removed if drain is plumbed through disposal (common missed step on new installs). Finally inspect drain pump impeller for debris — glass shards, broken plastic, and small utensils jam impellers. Pump replacement $245-$385 if impeller is damaged. Regular filter cleaning (monthly, or every 2 weeks for heavy use) prevents most E22/E24 calls.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>3. Dishes coming out wet — 800 Series CrystalDry issue</h3>
        <p>CrystalDry zeolite canister saturated. Zeolite mineral absorbs moisture and releases heat during dry cycle; over 4-6 years, the canister accumulates scale and detergent residue that reduces heat-release capacity. Symptoms: plastics especially not drying, heavier water residue on all dishes, rinse aid dispenser full but not helping. Canister replacement $285-$385. On older 800 Series units (pre-2020), verify it's actually the zeolite before ordering — heating element failure (E09 code) causes similar symptoms and is $185-$265.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>4. Dishwasher won't start, no response to button press</h3>
        <p>Five possibilities in order: (1) door not fully latched — push firmly until click; (2) Child Lock activated — hold button sequence per manual (model-specific); (3) Delay Start programmed — cancel via button sequence; (4) circuit breaker tripped (free reset); (5) door latch assembly failed ($145-$215 replacement). On 2020+ units with Home Connect, check the app — sometimes the unit is operating in remote-disabled mode if the app was recently configured. Firmware update resolves 15% of "won't start" complaints on 2021-2022 units without any parts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>5. Loud grinding or buzzing during wash cycle</h3>
        <p>Circulation pump or drain pump. Diagnostic: identify which sound corresponds to which phase. If noise during wash (water circulating through spray arms), it's the circulation pump ($285-$385). If noise during drain phase (water leaving dishwasher), it's the drain pump ($185-$265). On 10+ year old 500/800 Series, we recommend replacing both pumps as a preventive bundle ($440-$620) since they age similarly and a new pump next to a marginal pump causes repeat service within 12-18 months.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>6. E09 — oven not heating, rinse aid water spots</h3>
        <p>Heating element burnout. Tests 25-35 ohms good. When the element fails, cold water washes don't sanitize and rinse aid doesn't sheet off properly (spots on glassware). Element replacement $185-$265, 60-minute job. Alternative cause on 800 Series: heater relay solder joint on main control board — rare, but if element tests good, inspect the board for burn marks at the heater relay. Control board replacement $385-$580.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>7. Door won't close flush or gasket leaking</h3>
        <p>Door gasket wear or hinge drift. Gasket replacement $195-$285, 45-minute job. If hinge drift is the cause (door sagging, not closing parallel to frame), hinge realignment or replacement $145-$245 per hinge. On Bosch panel-ready SHV models, inspect the custom panel attachment — a heavy panel drags the door over time, accelerating hinge wear. We re-torque panel attachment hardware at the same service visit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>8. Spray arms not rotating or weak spray</h3>
        <p>Three causes: (1) spray arm jets clogged with hard-water scale (LA water 200-350 ppm accelerates this) — soak arm in vinegar overnight, clean ports with toothpick, free fix; (2) spray arm bearing worn — replacement $85-$165 per arm; (3) circulation pump weakening — if multiple arms weak and cleaning didn't help, pump $285-$385. We inspect all three before ordering parts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>9. E26 diverter motor fault</h3>
        <p>Diverter motor controls which rack's spray arms receive water — upper, lower, or both. When motor fails, one rack may get zero water (cleaning fails for that rack) or both racks constantly spray (cycle uses more water and takes longer). Replacement $145-$215, 60-minute job. Usually fails around year 7-10 on heavy-use units.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>10. Intermittent errors on 2021-2022 units — firmware issue</h3>
        <p>Known issue on 2021-2022 500/800 Series with Home Connect: firmware had intermittent handling bugs that Bosch addressed via over-the-air updates. Symptoms: random error codes that clear on reset then reappear days later, incomplete cycles, display freezing. First diagnostic step: check firmware version in Home Connect app, run update if available. About 15% of "intermittent error" calls on these units resolve via firmware without any parts. $85 flat for firmware service when that's all that's needed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── LA HARD WATER ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">LA-specific context</p>
      <h2>LA hard water and Bosch dishwasher maintenance</h2>
      <p>LA tap water runs 200-350 ppm of calcium and magnesium — well above what European-designed dishwashers like Bosch were originally calibrated for. The practical impact: scale buildup happens faster on Bosch dishwashers in LA than in softer-water markets, and service frequency reflects that.</p>
      <p>Specific LA-driven service items: E12 limescale warning appears at year 4-7 instead of year 8-10 in softer markets (descaling with Bosch Dishwasher Cleaner clears the code, $15 DIY); spray arm nozzle scale buildup requires vinegar soak every 6 months to maintain spray pressure; CrystalDry zeolite canister on 800/Benchmark saturates at year 4-6 vs year 6-8 elsewhere ($285-$385 replacement); heating element scale accumulation reduces efficiency and accelerates failure — LA 800 Series units often need heating element replacement at year 7-9 vs year 10-12 elsewhere.</p>
      <p>The water-softener setting matters but is often overlooked. Bosch dishwashers include a water softener (salt reservoir on some models; calibration setting on others). Ship from factory at a European-default setting that undertreats LA water. Our service visit includes verifying the softener setting matches local water hardness — a 2-minute adjustment that extends component life meaningfully. On units with salt reservoirs (Benchmark, some 800 Series), we verify salt level and refill frequency is adequate for LA conditions.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── PRICING ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Pricing</p>
      <h2>What Bosch dishwasher repair usually costs</h2>
      <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Labor and parts quoted separately before work starts.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical range</th></tr>
        </thead>
