      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Bosch dishwasher repair — common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>E15 on my Bosch — what do I do?</summary>
        <p>Anti-flood float switch triggered. Shut water supply off. Tilt Fix (tilt backward to drain pan) is not a repair — real leak still there. Find/repair leak source: inlet valve, Aquastop hose, gasket, pump seal. Float switch 00611316 (300/500/800) or 12019637 (Benchmark), $185-$265 + leak repair.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>E22 vs E24 vs E25</summary>
        <p>All drainage. E22 = fine filter blocked (clean filter, 80% free). E24 = drain hose/pump cover/garbage disposal plug. E25 = drain pump impeller blockage (glass shards typical). Monthly filter cleaning prevents most.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>800 Series CrystalDry not drying</summary>
        <p>Zeolite canister saturated at year 4-6 on LA hard water. Replacement $285-$385. If not CrystalDry issue: heating element (E09, $185-$265) or rinse aid empty (free).</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Home Connect firmware update — can it fix my issue?</summary>
        <p>Sometimes. 2020+ 500/800/Benchmark Series. 15% of intermittent errors on 2021-2022 units resolve via firmware without parts. $85 flat firmware service.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Is my Bosch dishwasher same as Thermador?</summary>
        <p>Yes — Thermador dishwashers are built on Bosch platform. Float switch 00611316 and circulation pump 00654575 identical. Service procedures identical. Only trim and branding differ.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does Bosch dishwasher repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common: circulation pump $285-$385, drain pump $185-$265, heating element $185-$265, float switch $185-$265, CrystalDry canister $285-$385, control board $385-$580. Full pricing above.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>My 100 Series has no display — how do I read errors?</summary>
        <p>Blinking-light patterns map to E-codes. Water-inlet flashing = E16/E17/E18. Drain light = E22/E24/E25. Door + start = E15. We carry code chart on every call — you don't need to decode.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

